    • isEncounterValidByAge

      public static boolean isEncounterValidByAge(Map<String,CoreCaseData> coreCaseDataByEncounterIdMap, UkbEncounter encounter, int upperAgeBorder)
      Checks if a given encounter is valid based on the patient's age at admission. An encounter is considered valid if it exists in the provided case data map and the age at admission is below the specified upper age limit.
      Parameters:
      coreCaseDataByEncounterIdMap - A map containing core case data indexed by encounter IDs. This map is used to check if the encounter is part of the dataset.
      encounter - The encounter to be validated against the age criteria.
      upperAgeBorder - The upper age limit for the encounter to be considered valid.
      Returns:
      true if the encounter is valid (exists in the map, and the age at admission is below the upper age limit); false otherwise.

    • getInpatientFacilityEncounters

      public static List<UkbEncounter> getInpatientFacilityEncounters(List<UkbEncounter> ukbEncounters)
      Filters the list of UkbEncounter objects to return only inpatient facility encounters.

      An encounter is considered an inpatient facility encounter if it meets the following criteria:

      • It is a facility contact (isFacilityContact() returns true).
      • It is not an outpatient case (isCaseClassOutpatient() returns false).
      • It is not semi-stationary (isSemiStationary() returns false).
      Additionally, the method adds a positive extension to each selected encounter.
      Parameters:
      ukbEncounters - the list of encounters to filter
      Returns:
      a list of inpatient facility encounters with the positive extension applied
